<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moravcik Against Special Status for Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik Against Special Status for Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005162694 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1300 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1300 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Slovak Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik discussed at a 
news conference held in Bratislava today the results of his 
official visits to France and Slovenia. Regarding the security 
situation in Europe, he stated that refusal to accept the Baltic 
state as members in the Partnership for Peace program will mean 
a violation of the fundamental principle underpinning the 
initiative, which is an individual approach and an equal 
opportunity for all states. According to Jozef Moravcik, the 
granting of special status to Russia will not be favorable for 
the countries of Central Europe, and it will signify to a 
certain extent a return to the idea of the division of the 
sphere of interests between Russia and the countries of the 
European Union or NATO. He added that if Slovakia were to be 
accepted as a member of the North Atlantic Alliance then the 
special status of Russia will not matter to us at all. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

