<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Milosevic Voted `Most Popular Personality' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Milosevic Voted `Most Popular Personality' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105150994 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1412 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Novi Sad, May 21 (TANJUG) -- Slobodan Milosevic, 
president of the Republic of Serbia, is the most popular 
personality in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (F.R.Y.), say 
the results of a poll published here on Saturday. The poll was 
conducted by the `Mark-Plan' marketing centre in 27 
muncipalities throughout the F.R.Y. on the basis of a 
representative sample of 1,045 persons of the different social 
and demographic profile. The questioned were asked to state five 
most popular public figures in the different fields, like 
politics, show business, sports, culture or the like. 
  The largest percentage (16.7 per cent) of the vote went to 
Slobodan Milosevic, followed by National Bank Governor Dragoslav 
Avramovic (7.3 per cent) who eliminated hyperinflation, and two 
folk music singers Dragana Mirkovic (6.9 per cent) and Lepa 
Brena (4.3 per cent). 
  As for other questions, 60 per cent of the answers said they 
would vote again for the political party they voted at last 
December's elections, while 48.6 and 29 per cent respectively 
believed and disbelieved in Dragoslav Avramovic's economic 
recovery program. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

