<H3> <TI>   New House of Counties Speaker Elected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New House of Counties Speaker Elected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305163694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Katica Ivanisevic is the new speaker of the 
Croatian Parliament's House of Counties, the chamber's deputies 
decided this afternoon. [passage omitted] 
  [Correspondent] The code of practice was amended by a 
majority vote to the effect that the chamber now has three 
deputy speakers. The majority party proposes the speaker of the 
chamber. Two deputy speakers are elected from the ranks of 
opposition parties and one from the majority party, at either 
the ruling HDZ's [Croatian Democratic Party] or opposition's 
proposal. The first deputy speaker is proposed by the 
opposition. [passage omitted] After Josip Manolic was relieved 
of duty by a majority vote, Professor Katica Ivanisevic of the 
HDZ was unanimously elected speaker of the chamber. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

