<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajina Serbs Want Akashi To Act as Mediator </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Krajina Serbs Want Akashi To Act as Mediator </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305142094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1308 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 23 May (TANJUG) -- Milan Martic, president of 
the republic of Serb Krajina [RSK], today received Enrico 
Agiliar, head of the civilian affairs section for UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] in Sector South, and proposed to him that 
UNPROFOR should take over the handling of the resumption of 
talks between Krajina and Croatia. Martic expressed 
dissatisfaction over the way this has been handled by Gehrt 
Ahrens and Kai Eide, deputy cochairmen of the conference on the 
former Yugoslavia, and proposed that Yasushi Akashi, the UN 
secretary-general's special envoy in Yugoslavia, take over as 
the coordinator to bring about the resumption of talks. 
  According to a statement by the RSK president's office, the 
two deputy cochairmen have acted as mediators in a tendentious 
and one-sided [as received] way and and have, in fact, only been 
passing on Croatian demands to the republic of Serb Krajina. 
President Martic said that mediation by a neutral and objective 
diplomat such as Yasushi Akashi would certainly produce certain 
results and would speed up the negotiating process between Knin 
and Zagreb. 

</TEXT>

