offering humanitarian and political aid to the people and the 
Government of Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Stressing that Iran is helping Bosnia-Herzegovina on the 
basis of friendship and not on the basis of religion and that it 
is doing so without setting any conditions, Prime Minister 
Silajdzic emphasized that there is no reason for concern in some 
circles because of this, since we, being a sovereign country, 
choose our friends and receive our guests. 
  Silajdzic hailed the idea of forming a tripartite commission 
for economic cooperation between (?Croatia), Iran, and 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

