BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 25 May (MTI) -- The Hungarian Foreign 
Ministry on Wednesday [25 May] asked MTI to publish the 
following statement: "The Foreign Ministry of the Republic of 
Hungary expresses concern over the Crimean situation, which 
carries the danger of aggravating tension and thus may have an 
impact on the stability of not only Ukraine but even its 
neighbors and friends. 
  "The Foreign Ministry welcomes and supports the efforts made 
by the sides concerned, primarily Ukraine, to settle the debate 
in a peaceful way, through negotiations. 
  "Hungary hopes that all steps made in the next days will be 
based on respect for the European scale of values and 
international law." 

