<H3> <TI>   New Relations Sought Between Army, Sejm </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Relations Sought Between Army, Sejm </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005165494 Warsaw PAP in English 1509 GMT 20 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2005165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, May 20 -- Deputy Defence minister 
responsible for parliamentary affairs Danuta Waniek said in an 
exclusive interview for PAP on Friday that she plans to give a 
"new shape" to the relations between the ministry and the Sejm 
and Senate. 
  She is going to establish a parliamentary office within the 
ministry that will draft laws necessary for the restructuring of 
the Polish Army. Waniek said she had already submitted her 
conception which is now being examined by the general staff. 
  Asked about the possibility to increase the role of women in 
the army, Waniek expressed the opinion that as soon as the 
Polish defence is built on professional army, the army will open 
to women in line with the constitutional principle of equal 
rights, "like in the United States," she said. 
  Referring to the question of civilian control over the army, 
Mrs. Waniek said that the control is in the hand of "the one who 
decides about the money," that is, the Sejm. Waniek also 
stressed that she did not suspend her membership in the Social 
Democracy of the Republic of Poland (SDRP). "Let the people 
know whom they have to do with" she said. 

</TEXT>

