<H3> <TI>   Moravcik Expresses Support for Nuclear Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik Expresses Support for Nuclear Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005193094 Prague CTK in English 1752 GMT 20 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2005193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava May 20 (CTK) -- Slovakia must make use 
of the "big" money it put into nuclear energy production, 
Premier Jozef Moravcik declared today. He said that the only 
possibility of doing this and at the same time respecting the 
opinion of neighbouring countries was to concentrate on the 
safety of nuclear power plant operations. "The project for 
completing the nuclear power plant in Mochovce, West Slovakia, 
is safer than the European average," Moravcik said. 
  Cooperation with France provides the possibility for 
securing 
Slovakia's basic interests in the energy producing sector and 
completing the Mochovce plant in a manner that would "serve as 
an example" of a safe solution, Moravcik added. 
  He stressed that the participation of the French and banking 
institutions in the Mochovce plant's completion was subject to 
the condition that operations would be stopped in the first 
reactor of another Slovak nuclear power plant located in 
Jaslovske Bohunice, West Slovakia. "The government has accepted 
the obligation," Moravcik stressed. 

