<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moslems, Croats Launch Tank Attacks on Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moslems, Croats Launch Tank Attacks on Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505023194 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2318 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505023194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Doboj, May 24 (TANJUG) -- Moslems and Croats on 
Tuesday afternoon [24 May] attacked Serb positions on all 
sections of the front from Doboj in the north of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, through central Bosnia-Herzegovina, to the 
line of delimitation in the area of Nevesinje in the south of 
this former Yugoslav republic, Bosnian Serb military sources 
said on Tuesday evening. Armed forces of Bosnian Croats, the 
Croatian Defense Council -- HVO, joined the Moslem forces with 
their tanks and attacked Serb positions in central Bosnia, 
REUTERS said on Tuesday evening, quoting sources of the United 
Nations Protection Force (UNPROFOR) in former Yugoslavia. 
  Bosnian Croat forces are actively helping Moslem troops 
against the local Serbs, REUTERS reported from Sarajevo. Two 
Croat T-55 tanks and HVO troops attacked Serb positions in a 
joint action southwest of Tesanj, REUTERS said. Two M-84 tanks 
also took part in this operation which began on Monday morning, 
said REUTERS quoting the same source. 
  Moslems forces are attacking serb defense positions and 
villages in fronts in the wider area of Doboj. In the afternoon 
hours, Moslems shelled Doboj and Serb villages and positions 
west of this town. 
  The Serb forces returned strong fire and neutralized the 
enemy operations. 
  On the front southeast of Teslic (south of Doboj), Moslem 
units have been trying to penetrate the Serb defense lines for 
days. 
  Moslems are speedily building up their forces south and 
southwest of Serb positions near Mt. Ozren (south of Doboj), the 
First Krajina corps of the Bosnian Serb Army said. United 
forces of the HVO and regular Croatian Army units on Tuesday 
fired several shells at Serb positions in the area of Gradine, 
on the front near Nevesinje (south of Mostar), TANJUG reported 
from Bileca on Tuesday evening, quoting a statement by the 
Herzegovina corps of the Bosnian Serb Army. The source also 
said that Serb fighters answered the attack, thus silencing the 
Croat guns. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

