<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Criticizes UN as Serbs Defy Sarajevo Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Criticizes UN as Serbs Defy Sarajevo Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505105994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2505105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Information Service of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Army 1st Corps has issued a statement saying that the enemy is 
still attacking on the Visoko, Vares, and Breza fronts. The 
Chetniks have been pounding Visoko from their positions in 
Dolipolje, Kriva, Jelica, and Siljak. The Vares area has also 
been exposed to heavy artillery fire, particularly the defense 
lines in (Mesevicko Brdo) the villages of Rokoc, [words 
indistinct], and the town itself. The aggressor has been using 
his entire artillery arsenal in these attacks, including 
howitzers, tanks, mortars, heavy guns, and antiaircraft guns and 
machine guns, from his positions in Brezac, Jeljani, [words 
indistinct]. 
  Several Chetnik infantry attacks on the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Army positions have been routed, but the enemy plans to continue 
to attack the free territory. This is [words indistinct] 
bringing in new forces and digging in. All these attacks and 
preparations have been under way in the exclusion zone, says the 
Army Press Center, and adds that -- considering such an indolent 
attitude of the UN Protection Forces -- the fighters and the 
units of our army are even more determined in their defense. 

</TEXT>

