<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Walesa, Oleksy Discuss Defense, Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa, Oleksy Discuss Defense, Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405173894 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1626 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 24 May -- Polish Republic President Lech 
Walesa had lunch at his residence with Sejm Speaker Jozef 
Oleksy, the president's press office reported today. They 
discussed the country's defense and security matters, the role 
of the Armed Forces supreme commander, and the need for a 
parliamentary debate on the issues with the participation of the 
president. 
  These matters should be discussed at the coming meeting of 
the National Defense Committee. It was also considered 
important that mechanisms be defined for political consultations 
on the security of the state. 
  The speaker also briefed the president on the parliament's 
agenda in the immediate future, before the summer recess. 
  Within the framework of the coordination of Polish foreign 
policy between the highest state authorities, the speaker 
discussed his planned visit to China, the communique says. 

</TEXT>

