<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe Confirms Slovene Attendance at Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Juppe Confirms Slovene Attendance at Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2405153794 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1330 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2405153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovene </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At today's news conference in Paris, French Foreign 
Minister Alain Juppe announced that Slovenia will be the only 
country from the former Yugoslavia at the Conference on 
Stability in Europe that will be given the status of a potential 
EU member. As REUTER reports, a decision about Slovenia's 
participation at this conference was made at the last moment, as 
our country was not on the list of nine invited central and 
Eastern European countries last week. 
  The French decision about this was also supported by 
Germany. 
It is known that our country, as opposed to Poland, the Czech 
Republic, Slovakia, Hungary, Romania, Bulgaria, Lituania, 
Latvia, and Estonia, has not signed the associate EU membership 
agreement yet. 

</TEXT>

