<H3> <TI>   Customs Corridor Preparations Almost Complete </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Customs Corridor Preparations Almost Complete </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2405155694 Skopje MIC in English 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2405155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Customs Corridor for Macedonia Next </F>
Month"] 
  [Text] The general director of the Romanian customhouse 
Mihai Panzaru said that Romania is close to finishing the 
preparations for the opening of a customs corridor for Macedonia 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM]. The 
realization of this endeavor is planned for the middle of next 
month. 
  The idea for a "customs corridor" which would connect 
Macedonia with the Western European countries, as it was 
emphasized in Bucharest, was given by the U.S. Administration, 
with the aim of helping Macedonia and carrying out its trade 
deals, which has been made difficult by the Greek embargo and 
the upholding of the sanctions against Federal Republic 
Yugoslavia. 
  Mihai Panzaru said "the corridor will span from Austria 
through Hungary, Romania, Bulgaria, to Macedonia." He added 
that Romania has already discussed this with the Hungarian 
authorities, while the Bulgarian side is also expected to be 
contacted these days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

