<H3> <TI>   Trial of 10 Albanians Begins in Skopje </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trial of 10 Albanians Begins in Skopje </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2405160294 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2405160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Paramilitary Trial Interrupted"] </F>
  [Text] The main hearing of the 10 Albanians, Macedonian 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] citizens, 
accused of forming paramilitary forces, started in Skopje, 
yesterday, with a proposition to abolish the imprisonment of 
suspects. Lawyers pointed out the court's right to hold them in 
custody has expired, which, as one lawyer stated, was anyhow 
opposed to the Macedonian constitution. Unless they are 
released, the defence threatened to demand disqualification of 
the District Court in Skopje, as well as of all other courts 
refusing to release the suspects. This proposal was rejected by 
the court with an explanation that the investigation procedure 
has been completed in due time, and the accusation has also been 
[words indistinct]. The hearing was interrupted after this, 
leaving time to the defence and the accused to discuss the 
demand for disqualification of the court. The next hearing is 
scheduled for May 30, and hearing of witnesses for June 7. Mr. 
Adolfo Ramirez, administrator of the U.S. Liaison Office in 
Skopje was also present at the hearing, as one of the suspects 
has double citizenship, Macedonian and American. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

