<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Dismisses Greek `Clamour' Over Arrests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Dismisses Greek `Clamour' Over Arrests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505103994 Tirana ATA in English 1019 GMT 25 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2505103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 25 (ATA) -- The spokesman of the Foreign 
Ministry reports that the recent clamour raised by the Greek 
Government regarding the announcement of the Tirana Attorney's 
Office about the reasons of the arrest of six Albanian citizens 
of Greek origin, as well as the statement of the spokesman of 
the Greek Government about this question are unjustifiable and 
do not serve the normalization of relations between the two 
countries and doubts their tones have a direct impact of 
electoral passions. 
  According to its statements, the Greek Government has 
undertaken and may undertake further steps towards international 
forums such as the [UN] Security Council, European Union, CSCE 
and other forums, interpreting this legal action of Albania as a 
violation of the rights of the Greek minority in Albania. 
  The spokesman of the Foreign Ministry of the Republic of 
Albania declares that the Albanian Government is ready to 
welcome the sending of commissions from the Security Council, 
CSCE, European Union and other institutions for a direct 
observation of the reality having in their disposal the complete 
file of the Albanian Attorney's Office as well as other 
documents which prove both the keeping of arms by these persons 
without permission and their relations with the Greek secret 
service as well as other unconstitutional and secessionist 
activities. However, this will not be in the interest of Greece 
and of the joint efforts the two countries are making to 
overcome the existing contradictions and problems. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

