<F P=102>   LD2405215894 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1630 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The delegation of the National Council of the 
Slovak Republic ended its official visit to Moscow, during which 
it extended an invitation to Ivan Rybkin, chairman of the lower 
chamber of the Russian State Duma, to visit Slovakia. Before 
leaving the Russian capital Jan Smihula, our resident 
correspondent, interviewed Ivan Laluha, chairman of the Duma's 
foreign committee. [passage omitted] 
  [Begin recording] [Smihula] There is a great deal of talk 
about Russia's role in the European security system and 
specifically about her special status within the Partnership for 
Peace program. 
  [Laluha] This was also the subject of our discussions. There 
is some confusion among Russian deputies because they have not 
been informed in a greater detail about the substance of the 
latest specific proposals put forward by representatives of the 
Russian Government. During our talks with the deputy foreign 
minister at the Foreign Ministry I received assurance that there 
do not exist any conditions from Russia either to NATO or to the 
Partnership for Peace program that could provoke fears about the 
security situation in our geopolitical area. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

