<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moravcik Chairs Coalition Council Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik Chairs Coalition Council Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405212294 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
2000 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405212294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Coalition Council met in Bratislava today 
under the chairmanship of Jozef Moravcik, the Slovak prime 
minister and chairman of the Democratic Union of Slovakia. It 
discussed the course to be taken by the Slovak Republic in the 
drafting of documents on the security initiative named as the 
pact of stability and other topical issues. Regarding 
Slovakia's participation in meetings of the stability pact, the 
Coalition Council agreed that Slovakia would be represented by a 
governmental delegation. This also applies to the opening 
meeting of the stability pact planned to take place next 
Thursday and Friday. The Coalition Council regard the solution 
of the problem of minorities as an internal matter of the state, 
although representatives of the Hungarian political parties 
voiced their demand to be allowed to participate in the meetings 
of the stability pact. However, it will be up to the government 
to decide who should form Slovakia's Government delegation. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

