<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bohunice Nuclear Power Reconstruction Outlined </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bohunice Nuclear Power Reconstruction Outlined </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2405130094 Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Slovak 19 May 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU2405130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Reconstruction of the Bohunice Nuclear Power </F>
Station"] 
  [Text] Bratislava -- The three stages of the gradual 
reconstruction of the V-1 nuclear power station at Jaslovske 
Bohunice will require costs of 11.3 billion korunas [Sk]. The 
first stage will involve the revalidation of safety-related 
installations and systems that are to be used in further 
operation of the unit. The second stage will focus on enhancing 
the capacity of the emergency systems and the cooling of the 
active zone for the primary circuit. The aim of the third stage 
is to enhance the capacity of the system for confining an 
accident. The reconstruction costs will be divided into 
individual years according to the cost-intensiveness of needed 
investments. A sum of Sk315 million will be appropriated in 
1994, Sk3.07 billion in 1995, Sk3.25 billion in 1996, Sk3.15 
billion in 1997, and Sk1.515 billion in 1998. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

