<H3> <TI>   Radiation Monitoring To Be Linked to Austria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radiation Monitoring To Be Linked to Austria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305121594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1000 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1000 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] A Slovak-Austrian agreement under which equipment 
for the exchange of data from the two countries' radiation early 
warning systems is to be linked in September this year was 
signed in Bratislava today. At present Austria has 336 radio 
measuring stations and Slovakia has 26. Under the agreement, 
data will be exchanged free of charge and provided to other 
authorities in both countries as well. 

