<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet, BSP Adopt Berov's Framework Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet, BSP Adopt Berov's Framework Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505173994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2505173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At an extraordinary closed meeting today, the 
government adopted the draft framework agreement with the 
parliament that was proposed by Prime Minister Berov. It will 
be in effect until new parliamentary and municipal elections are 
held in the fall. 
  The Executive Bureau of the Bulgarian Socialist Party [BSP] 
and the leadership of the BSP parliamentary faction discussed 
the framework agreement. It was agreed to support the segment 
that deals with setting a term for early parliamentary and 
municipal elections in the fall. The Socialists will also 
support the commitments of the Council of Ministers in the 
social sphere and its efforts to successfully end the 
negotiations on the country's foreign debt. They think the 
amendments to the Privatization Bill and a program on social and 
mass privatization should be adopted in June, while the Law on 
Defense and Armed Forces, amendments to the Election Bill, the 
Municipal Administration Bill, the Judicial Act, and the 
Constitution should be adopted in July. 
  In the decision that was adopted the Socialists committed 
themselves to supporting the personnel changes envisaged in the 
framework agreement and have proposed a candidate for the post 
of deputy prime minister. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

