<H3> <TI>   Katowice Miners: Solidarity `Playing Politics' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Katowice Miners: Solidarity `Playing Politics' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505211194 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
2000 GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Recent Solidarity strikes in hard coal collieries 
ended in complete disaster and humiliation for the organizers 
and the strike became a way of playing politics by Solidarity 
leaders at the expense of miners. Such is the opinion of a 
mining team of the August-80 Free Trade Union in Katowice. 
  For the first time the government coerced the strikers' 
representatives to accept the fact that strikers would not be 
paid for the period of the strike. In the team's opinion 
Solidarity leaders promised the strikers that they would be paid 
for the period of the strike. Currently, however, they are 
avoiding responsibility for the effects of the protest. 

</TEXT>

