  [Text] Warsaw, 25 May -- A three-day visit by a Chinese 
power industry delegation, headed by Deputy Minister Lu 
Yanchang, concluded on 25 May with the signing of an agreement 
on cooperation between the Polish Ministry of Industry and Trade 
and the Ministry of Power Industry of the People's Republic of 
China. 
  A working group to coordinate bilateral economic, trade, and 
technical and scientific cooperation in the power industry was 
set up. "We are interested in broader cooperation with the 
Chinese power industry and in trade with China. Investment 
credits will be granted for this purpose", said Herbert Gabrys, 
deputy minister of trade. 

