<H3> <TI>   Moravcik Defers Screening Government Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik Defers Screening Government Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505160194 Bratislava SME in Slovak 21 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2505160194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SME </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["mh"-signed report: "According to Prime Minister Moravcik, </F>
the Abolition of the Screening Law Is Out of the Question"] 
  [Excerpt] Bratislava -- [passage omitted] Asked by SME 
about his course of action regarding the request to have members 
of the coalition government screened, Prime Minister Jozef 
Moravcik replied that at present he cannot ask the Slovak 
Information Service [SIS] to issue screening certificates for 
government members because it would constitute an illegal act. 
Even though the prime minister had requested screenings, he did 
so on the basis of material law [hmotny zakon]. "After we 
realized that the procedural conditions had not been met, we 
agreed that the screening certificates would not be issued," 
Jozef Moravcik said. 

</TEXT>

