<H3> <TI>   New Movement Established, To Run Candidates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Movement Established, To Run Candidates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605082594 Bratislava SMENA in Slovak 20 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2605082594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SMENA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["ars"-signed report: "Tolerance Movement Established"] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Tolerance Movement [Hnutie Tolerancia, HT] 
was registered at the Ministry of Interior on 12 May. Two days 
later, it held its constituent congress. The movement's 
leadership, composed of chairwoman Anna Galovicova, PhD, deputy 
chairman Lubomir Sausa, and secretary Imrich Ciffra, visited our 
editorial office yesterday to inform us about the plans and 
goals of this new political entity. 
  The movement was established as a force of harmonization, 
whose task is to free us of emotional conflicts and campaign and 
post- election struggles. The HT wants to run in the early 
parliamentary elections independently, but it is not opposed to 
cooperation with other political entities either. It has 
launched a petition campaign to obtain the required number of 
signatures to participate in elections to the National Council 
of the Slovak Republic. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

