<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sead Susovic from the Information Service of the </F>
1st Army Corps] 
  [Excerpt] Counting probably on the factor of surprise, the 
chetniks carried out a strong attack on the city's defense lines 
in the Hladivode region late last night. This futile attack 
began with fierce shooting from light infantry weapons. The 
chetniks then started gradually to introduce anti-aircraft guns 
and machineguns, mortars, and similar types of weapons. The 
fighting culminated with the infantry attack, which the ever 
ready defenders of Sarajevo uncompromisingly repelled, forcing 
the chetniks to return to where they set off on their night 
adventure. The town is quiet this morning, but one must not 
forget to remain cautious. 
  The Ilijas front, which has been simmering with chetnik 
attacks for several days, was subjected to a fierce artillery 
attack during which more than 100 shells landed on [word 
indistinct] Brdo, [words indistinct] and other places in the 
free territory. The chetniks also carried out attacks from 
artillery and armored mechanized weapons from their position in 
Nisici, (?Buljetovac), Medojevici, Nabozici, (?Pudraz), and 
Duboki Potok. There are dozens of these weapons in this region. 
They are mainly inside the Sarajevo 20 km zone. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

