<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Woman Reportedly Killed by Muslim Shelling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Woman Reportedly Killed by Muslim Shelling </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505202194 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2008 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Sarajevo, May 25 (TANJUG) -- One woman was killed 
and 13 people were wounded in a Moslem artillery attack on the 
Sarajevo front on Tuesday [24 May] which grossly violated the 
truce, Bosnian Serb military sources have said. The command of 
the Sarajevo-Romanija corps of the Bosnian Serb army specified 
that Moslem forces fired 13 82mm-calibre mortar shells on the 
Srednje district on the Sarajevo-Olovo road and that one shell 
fell near a bus. The shell explosion killed one woman and 
injured 13 passengers, two of them seriously. 
  The woman was the 32nd victim in Serb-controlled areas of 
Sarajevo since a truce for Sarajevo was signed on February 9 
this year and the city was proclaimed an exclusion zone under 
protection of the United Nations Protection Force (UNPROFOR), 
the Bosnian Serb military sources said. The sources also said 
that 79 people were wounded in Moslem attacks, mostly from small 
arms, rifles with telescopic sights, and grenade launchers. The 
Moslem side is constantly violating the truce, primarily as a 
result of the complete lack of action by UNPROFOR who have not 
once reacted to warnings sent by the command of the 
Sarajevo-Romanija Corps of the Bosnian Serb army, the command 
said. 

</TEXT>

