<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Satellite Channel Threatened </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Satellite Channel Threatened </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505160694 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1156 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2505160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 25 May -- During today's meeting between the 
Sejm Commission for Liaison with Poles Abroad and the Senate 
Commission for Immigration and Poles Abroad, Leszek Wasiuta, the 
head of the satellite channel of Polish Television SA [TVP SA-- 
TVPolonia], said his channel was under threat because its status 
was not legalized in the broadcasting law. 
  That is why, in his opinion, TVP SA is not expected to be 
interested in investing TVP SA profits in TVPolonia as at 
present. He says the fact that TVPolonia was set up under Janusz 
Zaorski, the former head of the state radio and television, who 
was in conflict with the National Radio and Television 
Broadcasting Council [KRRiT], may affect this. 
  Danuta Celinska, TVP SA head of programming, has given 
assurances that the board had no intention of closing down 
TVPolonia; on the contrary "it is at the heart of our deepest 
and greatest interests." Also, KRRiT Head Ryszard Bender said 
that the council was not interested in closing down TVPolonia. 

</TEXT>

