<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Radio Reports Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarajevo Radio Reports Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605144194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2605144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] After yesterday and last night's bestial shelling 
of Bihac and the outskirts of Cazin, the joint aggressors today 
continued their attacks on the Bihac Commune. The chetniks are 
using mortars and howitzers of all calibers to shell the forward 
defense lines on the Grmusko-Srbljanski plateau and Grabez, 
while on Hasin Vrh and Vrsak they continue attempts at infantry 
breakthroughs. The 5th Corps members are energetically 
resisting, and the defense lines remain stable. On the other 
parts of the front, they continued using antiaircraft weapons, 
while sniper fire and small arms' fire has intensified. 
  The members of Abdic's paramilitary army are also not quiet. 
They are increasingly collaborating with their allies. In the 
wider area of Trsak, Viskovac, and Todorovo, they haven been 
concentrating fresh forces and hardware since yesterday, and are 
preparing fresh attacks in collaboration with the chetniks. In 
the course of the day, they have been intensifying activity on 
all demarcation lines, using small arms, antiaircraft arms, and 
armor-piercing weapons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

