<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Recaptures Territory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Recaptures Territory </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705095994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2705095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] Throughout last night and this morning chetnik 
artillery has been pounding the Bihac area. From their 
strongholds in Veliki (Radic), and Grabez, the chetniks have 
been shelling parts of this UN protected zone with howitzers and 
mortars, and trying to conceal this behind the [words 
indistinct] conflict caused by Abdic's traitor clique. 
  Dozens of shells were fired overnight at the outskirts of 
Bihac, while the defense lines on the Grmusko-Srbljanski 
plateau, Hasin Vrh, and Grabez have been under continuous mortar 
fire. In decisive counterattacks, the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 
5th Corps has recaptured some of the territory on the plateau, 
inflicting heavy losses on the chetniks in manpower, and 
capturing a large amount of ammunition and equipment. This must 
have been the reason for the start of the chetniks' bestial 
shelling of civilian targets, which also served as a sign to the 
Kladusa traitor paramilitaries to intensify their own attacks on 
the areas of [word indistinct], Pecigrad, (Liskovac), and 
Todorovo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

