<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rose Clarifies Statement on Army's Weakness </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rose Clarifies Statement on Army's Weakness </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605201094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2605201094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The statement made yesterday by the UN Protection 
Forces [UNPROFOR] commander [General Rose] that the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army did not have the strength to retake the 
lost territories met with widespread, mostly negative, 
reactions. That is why we were informed by the Office of the 
President of the Presidency that during last night's talks [with 
General Rose], President Izetbegovic asked General Michael Rose 
to explain his statement. 
  The British general supplemented his earlier remark by 
saying 
that he had also told the Serbs they could not win under any 
conditions. Their infantry is irreparably wounded, said General 
Rose, and in the long run, they would [word indistinct] lose the 
war in Bosnia. The UNPROFOR commander in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
believes that, at the moment, the Serbs cannot defeat the 
Bosniaks, while the Bosniaks do not have the strength to expel 
the occupiers. A firm stalemate has been created in Bosnia, 
which, according to General Rose, is forcing both sides to look 
for a compromise to end the conflict. This is stated in the 
communique issued by the Office of the President of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

