<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gradacac Reportedly Faces Renewed Serb Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gradacac Reportedly Faces Renewed Serb Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705094294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2705094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by the Information Service of the 107th Chivalrous </F>
Motorized Gradacac Brigade] 
  [Text] This morning goes to prove the well-known fact that 
the relative quiet in Gradacac is a delusion, as the aggressor 
can turn this front quickly and suddenly into a scene of total 
war. Gradacac and the surrounding area have been vibrating to 
the thunder of heavy shells exploding since 0530 this morning. 
The enemy launched this extremely powerful artillery attack 
from Gornje Krecane with three tanks, 82-mm and 120-mm mortars, 
recoilless guns, and all kinds of antiaircraft weapons. At the 
time of this report, over 500 shells have already landed on the 
defense lines in Novalici, (Osmanovici), and Vida. Over 50 have 
been directed at the town center. 
  This situation reminds us of the time of July 1992. Gradacac 
is experiencing true hell. This is the worst morning of the war 
this year. 
  At about 0800 the chetniks launched an infantry attack at 
the 
area of (Osmanovici), but it was successfully repelled. [words 
indistinct] Jasenica, and Rajska also came under a very heavy 
artillery, infantry, and armored attack early this morning. As 
we report, the situation on the front is deteriorating further 
and the attacks seem to be intensifying. The aggressor is 
firing howitzers at the town center. But despite everything the 
defense lines are firm and stable. 

</TEXT>

