<H3> <TI>   Eastern Mostar Gets First Electricity Supplies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Eastern Mostar Gets First Electricity Supplies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705112194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2705112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the latest information from the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Electricity Board, the technical conditions 
have been created for the eastern part of Mostar to receive one 
megawatt of electricity. This amount is sufficient for priority 
consumers, and there will also be some distributed to the 
general public, insofar as this can be done through the very 
badly damaged distribution network. Repairs are under way on 
two more facilities to provide Mostar with electricity. At the 
same time work is under way on repairing the street lights and 
the first light bulb has already started to illuminate Mostar. 

</TEXT>

