<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shops, Businesses Closed as Army Shells Doboj </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shops, Businesses Closed as Army Shells Doboj </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705112094 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2705112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, by 1100, a general danger alarm had been 
sounded three times in Doboj as Muslim [Bosnia-Herzegovina Army] 
artillery constantly shelled the city center from the direction 
of Tesanj. The fiercest Muslim attacks in the last few months 
started shortly after 0800 this morning. They were stepped up 
at 0900, and after a brief break, resumed at 1030. More than 10 
tank and mortar shells landed on and around the city center area 
during this period. According to first reports, the material 
damage is considerable. There are no reports on possible 
casualties yet, although ambulances are to be heard in the town. 
Owing to the artillery attacks on the town yesterday and today, 
schools, shops, businesses, and other public institutions are 
not functioning in Doboj. Only the hospital, the police, and 
the civil defense are working. This has been a report by our 
correspondent Brane Bozic. 

</TEXT>

