<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Barred From Inspecting Cargo at Tuzla </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Barred From Inspecting Cargo at Tuzla </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705104194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0845 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, 27 May (TANJUG) -- The Muslim side has 
not allowed a representative of the republic of Srpska army to 
take part in the inspection of cargo at Tuzla's Dubrave airport. 
The cargo is for UN Protection Force [UNPROFOR] units and 
reportedly it also contains humanitarian aid for the Muslim 
side, it was learned today in circles of the republic of Srpska 
army. 
  It has been agreed with UNPROFOR's mediation that one 
representative of the republic of Srpska army will inspect every 
plane cargo. However, since the agreement was cancelled, cargo 
has continued to arrive by planes with no control. No one has 
said anything about what will happen to the agreement. This 
example shows how much the Muslims care to substantiate the 
assurances that no military equipment is being shipped to Tuzla 
airport, that is, how much goodwill there is to take part in 
peace processes, the republic of Srpska army circles say. 

</TEXT>

