<F P=102>   AU2605194494 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2605194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Governor of the National Bank of Yugoslavia 
Dragoslav Avramovic has held talks with the businessmen and 
trade union leaders of the Rakovica commune. Concluding that 
production could be increased on the basis of consumer loans, 
he, at the same time, announced their introduction. Dragoslav 
Avramovic stressed that it is encouraging that we have noted a 
drop in unemployment for the first time since the outbreak of 
the war on the territory of the former Yugoslavia. He added 
that the policy of the National Bank of Yugoslavia is determined 
by the fact that more than half of the capacities in the economy 
are unexploited, while the reserves in the labor force are also 
great. Dragoslav Avramovic is of the opinion that company 
profits should be taxed and not salaries. 

</TEXT>

