<H3> <TI>   Payne Opposes Russian NATO Proposals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Payne Opposes Russian NATO Proposals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605172194 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1500 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] If NATO remains faithful to its original ideas in 
the Partnership for Peace program, it will not accede to Russian 
demands, said Jiri Payne, chairman of the parliament's foreign 
affairs committee, in reaction to Russian demands that the 
Partnership for Peace agreement be accompanied by a treaty 
guaranteeing a system of consultation between Russia and NATO. 
Payne described as rather shocking the notion that Russia should 
take part in decisions concerning the expansion of NATO to 
include Central and Eastern Europe. 

