<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   MDF, KDNP Reach Accord on Second Round </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MDF, KDNP Reach Accord on Second Round </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605130794 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1000 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Hungarian Democratic Forum [MDF] and the 
Christian Democratic People's Party [KDNP] have concluded a 
cooperation agreement for the second round of the elections. 
Under the Christian-democratic agreement, they are to back the 
candidates of the Independent Smallholders' Party [FKGP] in some 
places as well. Agnes Pap reports. 
  [Pap] [passage omitted] MDF Spokesman Karoly Herenyi said 
that not only was joining forces between the parties at issue 
but also the necessity to make a broader agreement. The leading 
bodies of the KDNP and the MDF want the Christian-democratic 
pooling of forces to come about among the voters, including 
those who voted for the FKGP. 
  Herenyi said that the MDF's voters would support the FKGP's 
candidates in 42 places where they have a chance to win. Under 
agreements concluded with the FKGP county chairmen in Somogy and 
Tolna counties [southern Hungary], the FKGP candidates are to 
support the MDF candidates in five places. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

