<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Warns of Yugoslav `Pressure' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Warns of Yugoslav `Pressure' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705102394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0739 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 27 May (TANJUG) -- Media in Skopje report 
today that Defense Minister Vlado Popovski has said that the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia is preparing a new scenario of 
exerting pressure on The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
[FYROM] by encouraging disputes on the border between Serbia and 
FYROM. Popovski said this in an address yesterday to officers 
of the FYROM Army. 
  After the plan to create Serbian regions in Macedonia 
failed, 
the idea of the border being a problem is now favored in Serbian 
circles, although under the Constitutions of both the Federal 
People's Republic of Yugoslavia and the Socialist Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia the [former Yugoslav] republics were 
treated as states, Popovski said. Talking to the officers, 
Minister Popovski denied the worldwide belief that FYROM has 
become an American aircraft carrier, and that America's military 
presence on its territory threatens the security of its 
neighbors. 

</TEXT>

