<H3> <TI>   Baudys on Army Officers Accused of Collaboration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baudys on Army Officers Accused of Collaboration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505092694 Prague CTK in English 2019 GMT 24 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2505092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, May 24 (CTK) -- Defense Minister Antonin 
Baudys said today it had not yet been proved that there were 
officers in the Czech Army who did collaborate with the former 
communist state police (StB). In an interview with CTK Baudys 
thus reacted to a statement by parliamentary Deputy Tomas Fejfar 
who said that Baudys had confirmed that the lustration or 
screening law had been violated in the army in the case of at 
least two high-ranking officers. 
  Baudys told CTK that both he and Fejfar had been separately 
briefed on the "suspicion that there are officers in the army 
who though being found to have collaborated with StB were 
granted positive or clear lustration certificates. "I have 
ordered the checking of all documents concerning the lustration 
law and nothing of the kind had thus far been proved," Baudys 
said. 
  Nova television, which today broadcast an interview with 
Fejfar, reported on Monday that the lustration law was being 
grossly violated in the Czech Army High Command and that 
positively lust rated officers produce negative lustration 
certificates. 

</TEXT>

