<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, May 26 (CTK) -- Interior Minister Jan Ruml 
says in an interview for today's left-leaning RUDE PRAVO that he 
knows for certain that General Karel Pezl, former head of the 
Czech Army's General Staff and now an adviser to Defense 
Minister Antonin Baudys, has a clean screening (lustration) 
certificate. Ruml said he believed that the result of the 
screening of General Rostislav Kotil, head of the South sector 
of the UNPROFOR forces in Croatia, would be the same. 
  He was reacting to recent media allegations that both 
generals had failed the screening tests which must be taken by 
all persons in or entering high office to see if they had 
collaborated with or been an agent of the former communist 
secret police. These allegations were confirmed by Tomas Fejfar 
(ODS), deputy chairman of parliament's defense and security 
committee, on May 24, but Baudys does not agree. 
  Ruml also confirmed that Baudys had taken an interest in the 
results of Pezl's test. He said it had not yet been shown that 
officers who failed their screening tests were working in the 
army. "I have ordered a new inspection of all the documents 
concerning the screening law to be carried out, and nothing like 
this has been shown yet," Ruml told CTK on May 24. 

