<F P=103> AU2505170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, May 25 (CTK) -- The Czech Government today 
approved legal measures aimed at transferring state-owned real 
estate to the ownership of the Federation of Jewish Communities 
and Jewish Religious Communities, Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus 
told journalists after a cabinet meeting. 
  Individual ministries ought to submit their proposals for 
specific transfers to the Finance Ministry for definitive 
approval by June 15, Klaus said. The State Jewish Museum makes 
an exclusion since in its case, given the complicated nature of 
the transfer, a proposal should be submitted only in September, 
he added. 
  Klaus confirmed that all the transfers would be implemented 
in the form of a gift-given agreement according to the Civil 
Code. 

</TEXT>

