<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Free Democrats Seeking `Social Peace' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Free Democrats Seeking `Social Peace' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705075394 Budapest MTI in English 1455 GMT 26 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2705075394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 26 May (MTI) -- "The next government -- 
whether a coalition or not -- should strive to create social 
peace, which can best be done if balanced power relations evolve 
as a result of the parliamentary elections," Gabor Fodor, ranked 
second on the national election list of the Alliance of Free 
Democrats (SZDSZ), told a news conference in Budapest on 
Thursday. 
  The SZDSZ does not approve of a single party determining the 
work of the next parliament instead of a sensible compromise 
between various political parties, as compromises always have 
greater social support than the decisions of one party, Fodor 
said. 
  SZDSZ campaign chief Balint Magyar stated that electors will 
determine what coalition opportunities exist after the second 
round of voting on May 29, and whether the balance of different 
political forces will be ensured within the new government. 
  The SZDSZ is aware that the country needs a balanced 
government which is able to put an end to social division. 
During coalition talks after the run-off elections, the Free 
Democrats will strive to help the emergence of a new government 
with a large social following, ready to deal with economic 
questions instead of ideological debates. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

