<H3> <TI>   Election Results Schedule Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Election Results Schedule Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705091394 Budapest MTI in English 0656 GMT 27 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2705091394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 27 May (MTI) -- After examining possible 
complaints and granting legal redresses, the National Electoral 
Committee is to announce the final result of the 1994 
parliamentary elections in 10 to 14 days after the May 29 second 
round, Ilona Palffy, deputy head of the Interior Ministry's 
Electoral Office, told MTI. 
  Under the Constitution, the president of the Republic is to 
convene the founding session of the new parliament in 30 days 
after the elections. The session will mark the end of the 
mandate of the government in office. In the subsequent 40 days, 
parliament will pass a decision on the prime minister candidate 
proposed by the president of the republic and on the program of 
his government, Palffy said. 
  Should the prime minister candidate and his program be 
accepted by a majority of deputies, the new prime minister will 
make proposals for the ministers, who will then be appointed by 
the president. This means that Hungary may have a new 
government by late July, she said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

